							<div class="panel-body">
								<p>The three-day audition camps are for providing full auditions and evaluations of prospective members with the intent of finalizing membership in the Colts. You will receive detailed instruction on all aspects of your skills with the intent of offering you membership, or guidance on how to become a member of the Colts. After attending one of these camps you will receive a letter officially notifying you of your membership status in the corps. See “JOIN” below for further details.</p>
								<p>Offers of full membership will be extended following each three-day audition camp. If there are special circumstances that make attendance at one of these events impossible, first <a href= "rsvp.html" target= "blank">RSVP</a> and then contact your caption head to express your interest in a spot, and to discuss preparations you should make for the next rehearsal (for color guard, this could be in April following WGI).</p>
                            
								<p><strong>April 28-30, 2017</strong> | Dubuque, IA<br>
								7:00 PM Friday through 4:00 PM Sunday <em>(brass, percussion, and color guard)</em></p>
