				<h3 class="section-title">Prepare</h3>
				<ol>
					<li>Prepare for your audition. Audition packets will be sent via email after you fill out an <a href= "inforequest.php" target="blank">Information Request</a></li>
					<li>Attend rehearsal! <strong>Always check the home page at <a href="http://colts.org/">colts.org</a> within a few hours of leaving for camp!</strong> Any updates or changes will always be posted here first. Specific monthly rehearsal information is released a week or so prior to each rehearsal. Camps are held monthly at a middle school in Dubuque, at the Five Flags Civic Center in downtown Dubuque, or in the Kansas City area.</li>
					<li>Become familiar with our <a href="schedule-preseason.html" target="blank">calendar</a>. Our pre-season schedule is limited, so attendance is important. Attending part of the camp is better than not at all. If you have conflicts, talk to us, we will work with you! <strong>COMMUNICATION IS CRITICAL!</strong></li>
				</ol>
				<p>The cost for your first rehearsal is $175 (or $125 for returning members) which includes all audition and application fees. <strong><a href="http://store-colts-org.3dcartstores.com/Camp-Fees_c_28.html" target="blank">Pay the fees online for your first camp in advance and SAVE $25</a></strong>. <em>Deadline for advance payment discount for the camps is the Tuesday immediately before a camp at 11:00 p.m.</em> Each subsequent weekend you attend is $60. This fee covers the cost of these rehearsals and does not apply toward your summer tuition.</p>
				
				<h3 class="section-title">Join</h3>
				<p>Following your first rehearsal, you will receive a letter from us that will be one of the following:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>An offer of full membership for the upcoming season.</li>
					<li>A recall for a second and final audition because we need to see you make improvements in specific areas of your performance or conditioning.</li>
					<li>An offer to continue to come to camps so that you can continue to improve your skills in the event that a spot opens up during the winter or spring. If no spot opens up, you are encouraged to take what you learn so that you can audition again next year.</li>
				</ul>
				
				<p>Try at least one weekend before deciding anything about the Colts. <strong>A life-changing summer of travel, achievement and success awaits you.</strong> Being here will make that happen. <em>You'll never know if you don’t try!</em></p>
             </div>
			</section>
